# CS3388 Assignment 4 – Textured Mesh House

Name: Muniver Kaur Kharod  
Student Number: 251425117  
Course: CS3388  
Assignment: Assignment 4 – Textured Mesh Rendering

## Overview

This program loads and renders a 3D house scene using OpenGL. The scene is made up of multiple meshes stored as .ply files and textures stored as .bmp files. Each mesh is loaded from file, uploaded to the GPU using vertex buffer objects (VBOs), and rendered using vertex array objects (VAOs) and shaders.

A simple first-person camera is implemented so the user can move through the scene using the arrow keys.

Main goals:
- Load meshes from .ply files
- Load textures from .bmp files (using the provided BMP loader)
- Use modern OpenGL (VBOs, VAOs, shaders)
- Implement a movable first-person camera
- Render transparent objects correctly using alpha blending and draw order

## Project Structure

In my working setup, the code and assets are stored in the project folder, while the README and screenshots were created as separate files/folders (outside the project folder). For submission, everything can be placed together or zipped together.

Project folder contents:

CS3388_AS4/
  src/        C++ source + header files  
  shaders/    Vertex + fragment shaders  
  assets/     .ply meshes + .bmp textures  

Separate items:
  README.md
  screenshots/   (screenshots of the final rendering)

## How to Compile (Mac, Homebrew)

From the project folder:

cd ~/Downloads/CS3388_AS4

Compile with:

g++ -std=c++17 -O2 src/*.cpp -I/opt/homebrew/include -L/opt/homebrew/lib -lglfw -lglew -framework OpenGL -o a4

Note: On my machine, brew --prefix outputs /opt/homebrew, so the include/lib paths above match my Homebrew install.

## How to Run

After compiling, run:

./a4

When it starts, the program prints messages like:

Reading image assets/bottles.bmp  
Reading image assets/curtains.bmp  
...  

This confirms that the BMP textures were found and loaded.

## Camera Controls

The camera starts at position:

(0.5, 0.4, 0.5)

and initially looks in the direction:

(0, 0, -1)

Controls:

Up Arrow      Move forward  
Down Arrow    Move backward  
Left Arrow    Rotate camera left  
Right Arrow   Rotate camera right  
ESC           Exit the program

Movement/rotation happens continuously while keys are held down.

## Rendering Approach

- Each mesh is loaded from a .ply file using a custom readPLYFile function.
- Vertex positions and UVs are uploaded to the GPU using VBOs.
- Triangle indices are uploaded using an element buffer object (EBO).
- A VAO stores the attribute configuration so it only needs to be set once during mesh creation.
- Textures are loaded from .bmp files using loadARGB_BMP and uploaded to OpenGL.

All meshes share the same shader program, which performs simple texture mapping using an MVP matrix.

## Transparency Handling

Alpha blending is enabled using:

glEnable(GL_BLEND);
glBlendFunc(GL_SRC_ALPHA, GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);

To ensure transparency renders correctly, the following meshes are drawn after all opaque meshes:

Curtains  
MetalObjects  
DoorBG  

Depth writes are temporarily disabled while drawing transparent objects to reduce visual artifacts.

## Assets Used

Bottles.ply / bottles.bmp  
Curtains.ply / curtains.bmp  
DoorBG.ply / doorbg.bmp  
Floor.ply / floor.bmp  
